<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Despite delivering an explosive episode filled with glamour and drama, The Bachelor's semi-final ratings were a disappointment.</p>

<p>Channel 10's hit reality dating show - currently in its eighth season - was the fourth most viewed program across the country for the 7pm timeslot on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The most watched show of the night was ABC's Hard Quiz, which pulled in an impressive 729,000 viewers according to TV Tonight.</p>

<p>Bomb: Channel 10's The Bachelor was the fourth most viewed program across the country for the 7pm timeslot on Wednesday night</p>

<p>It was followed by Channel Nine's renovation reality series was second with 701,000 viewers, while news program 7:30 hit 637,000.</p>

<p>The Bachelor limped in at fourth place, attracting 584,000 viewers.</p>

<p>It's a huge drop from last season's semi-final with Matt Agnew, which attracted 803,000 viewers last year.</p>

<p>Much better: It's a huge drop from last season's semi-final with Matt Agnew (pictured), which attracted 803,000 viewers last year</p>

<p>Despite The Bachelor's poor ratings, the episode was still the No. 1 show of the night among viewers under 50.</p>

<p>The much-anticipated finale of The Bachelor on Thursday night will see Locky Gilbert choose between Irena Srbinovska and Bella Varelis. </p>

<p>He recently shit down rumours that he's no longer dating the winner, telling New Idea he was '110,000 per cent in love' with his chosen contestant. </p>

<p>Popular: The most watched show of the night was ABC's Hard Quiz, which pulled in an impressive 729,000 viewers according to TV Tonight </p>

<p>'Excited is an understatement,' Locky said of finally being able to reveal his girlfriend.</p>

<p>'I cannot wait. I am beyond excited to be able to finally say it out loud... who I have chosen to spend the rest of my life with.' </p>

<p>According to betting odds, Irena is predicted to win, although there's still a chance that Bella could leave with Locky in an upset. </p>

<p>Finale: Irena Srbinovska (left)  and Bella Varelis (right) are set to battle it out for Locky Gilbert's heart on Thursday</p>
